# Homie k3s kubectl identity (read-only)

## Default kubeconfig for the agent

Always set:

```bash
export KUBECONFIG="$HOME/.kube/homie-k3s-readonly.yaml"
```

(or `$HOME/.kube/homie-k3s.yaml` only if it is the readonly install from
`scripts/mint-homie-k3s-readonly-kubeconfig.sh`).

| File | Who |
|------|-----|
| `~/.kube/homie-k3s-readonly.yaml` | **Agent default** — SA `homie-ops/homie-readonly` → ClusterRole `view` |
| `~/.kube/homie-k3s-admin.yaml` | **Break-glass only** — human operator; agent must not use |

## Forbidden for the agent

- `KUBECONFIG=~/.kube/homie-k3s-admin.yaml` (or any admin/client-cert context)
- `kubectl` writes (`apply`, `create`, `patch`, `edit`, `delete`, `set`, `rollout restart`, `scale`, `exec`, `cp`, `port-forward` that imply write paths you do not need)
- Minting/replacing kubeconfigs unless the user explicitly asked

If a task needs a write (secrets apply, RBAC change, Workflow submit that fails under `view`), **stop** and tell the user to run it with admin / break-glass — do not switch identities yourself.

## Allowed

- `get` / `describe` / `logs` / `top` / `auth can-i`
- Argo status reads (`kubectl -n argocd get app …`)
- Diagnosing OutOfSync / image pin / pod readiness

Desired-state changes: git → push → Argo auto-sync (see `no-manual-cluster-mutation.mdc`).

## Re-mint (human)

```bash
KUBECONFIG=~/.kube/homie-k3s-admin.yaml \
  ./scripts/mint-homie-k3s-readonly-kubeconfig.sh --apply --install-default
```
